I’m just so frustrated about all this. Because of the limitations of insurance companies, I was robbed over a decade of my life, my fertility was stolen from me, and now I’m even too sick to adopt a child. I’m only 35. I will never get better. All my illnesses are progressive.

Come to find out I had plantar fasciitis in an odd place in my foot and physical therapy would have actually damaged my tendons and other connective tissue. It was already pulling the bone below my pinkie toe out of place a little.
My dr had to fight for an MRI on my foot because an X-ray wasn’t showing the source of pain. They requested I do physical therapy first. FIRST, WITHOUT KNOWING WHAT THE PROBLEM EVEN WAS!
Being denied drug coverage, important diagnostic tests, and refusing to cover certain specialists? What credentials do they have that allows them to over ride a doctor’s request.
But my point is, insurance companies are actively killing people and it goes beyond this inconvenience I am going to be experiencing in a few hours.

I’m unvaccinated because of my reactions to vaccines in the past. It was life threatening. I am actively talking to my doctor about it and getting referrals to specialists to try and figure out if it’s safe specially for my body.

I have a uterus that sporadically bleeds. I can’t go on long car trips because of this. But I’m forced to. I’m also one of the unvaccinated immunocompromised. I can’t just stop anywhere on the way to see my dr.

It’s just weird to me how easy it was for everyone to create accommodations during the peak of the pandemic and now that vaccines are a thing they are yanking them away. Zoom appointments were working! And they were continent! 🤦

Insurance companies are forcing doctors to go back to mandatory office visits unless people have respetory symptoms. I have a dr appointment today. I’m in the worst cfs flare of my life. Walking to the 🚽 is hard. Lifting my armS is hard. My 🚗 ride is 45 mins. It will HURT.
